        "message": "LU-3536 osp: cancel logs after all updates committed\n\nCancel all update logs after all updates has been committed\n\nDuring cross-MDT operation, master MDT will execute update\nfirst, and get the transno and logcookie of these updates and\nsend them to the slave MDT, so updates recorded on slave MDT\nwill include transno both on Master MDT and slave MDT, by which,\nthe slave MDT will know whether these updates have been committed on\nboth MDTs. If all of them have been committed, the slave MDT will\n\n1. cancel local update log, which has been committed to disk.\n2. send logcookie to the master MDT, which will cancel the update\nlog on the master MDT.\n\nSigned-off-by: wang di <di.wang@intel.com>\nChange-Id: Ida314d3cf3bb2fef67f0d04ad2c0d06e3a1d225c\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
